name: SNKRS Day Brown
title: Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown
description:
In honor of the annual "SNKRS Day" celebration, Nike designed the Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown model released in 2020. The Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown features brown, tan, beige, and khaki colors, and includes a blend of leather and mesh materials. The heels of the Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown get a date stamp in honor of SNKRS Day, and the outsoles feature a color combination that mixes white, tan, and brown.

The Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown released in August 2020 and retailed for $140.

name: Grey Iron Island Green
title: Represent x StockX Bully Sneaker (Edition of 300) Grey Iron Island Green
description: The StockX x Represent Bully collaboration celebrates the coming together of both StockX and Represent to offer an exclusive capsule for the enthusiast & collectors alike. Limited to just 300 units worldwide and developed on the latest Represent Bully model, these sneakers feature StockX colours, combining iconic style and exclusivity. Elevate your sneaker collection with this remarkable collaboration. The Bully, a retro skate-inspired sneaker. It features a ballistic nylon mesh upper, with luxury leather and suede overlays. It exhibits Represent’s initial logo in an all-over fashion on a TPU exoskeleton, with complex stitching and a final initial logo worked into the heel of the shoe. A padded collar and chunky lacing reinforce the fierce aesthetic, whilst the two-tone skate-inspired outsole unit fortifies ultimate comfort.

title: Balenciaga Track White Orange
description: The Balenciaga Track White Orange is a highly sought-after sneaker that was released on September 3, 2018, with a retail price of $1120. This shoe features a white and orange colorway that is eye-catching and unique. The upper is made of a combination of mesh, nylon, and rubber materials, which provide both durability and breathability. The shoe also features a chunky sole that is both comfortable and stylish. One of the standout features of the Balenciaga Track White Orange is its attention to detail. The shoe features a complex layering system that creates a dynamic and textured look. The orange accents on the shoe add a pop of color that makes it stand out from other sneakers on the market. Something we love about the Balenciaga Track White Orange is its ability to blend fashion and function seamlessly. The shoe is not only stylish but also comfortable and practical for everyday wear. Our experts think that the best features of this shoe are its unique design and attention to detail. If you're looking for a statement piece that will turn heads, the Balenciaga Track White Orange is the perfect choice.

name: Sneakersnstuff
title: New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff
description:
Sneakersnstuff and New Balance have been collaborating since 2005, releasing projects with robust storylines that represent their Stockholm background. The shop is taking a different approach to their upcoming 920 release, with a theme around vintage 1990s sportswear and old-school, "Mom & Pop" sporting goods shops.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff brings out quality materials to the new running silhouette. The sneaker is composed of a mix of forest green and orange pigskin suede. From there, hits of 3M appear on the toe and heel, while New Balance’s logo is embroidered in yellow on the tongue and heel. Finally, the midsole is constructed for comfort, featuring New Balance’s signature ENCAP cushioning system.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff released in January of 2021 for $200.

The footwear features a white leather upper with black writing that reads "collar," "swoosh," "toe," "quarter," "cupsole," and more. The Nike swoosh is on the footwear side and the Jumpman logo is on the Jordan wings and tongue. The footwear has a white midsole fitted with a black rubber outsole. The black color on the outsole is the only thing that contrasts the white upper.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) sold at a retail price of $100 and was released on March 29th, 2022.

name: Sneaker Politics Always Ready

description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard design was inspired by Sneaker Politics Founder and CEO Derek Curry’s time in the Army. This pair features rich green/black canvas colorway underlays that mimic military gear, including Neoprene detailing with an American flag pattern at the toe box and an embroidered Politics letter "P" branding at the heel.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard silhouette retains its signature split-tongue formation and has a comfortable rubber outsole with GEL technology for optimal impact absorption.

ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard launched in May 2022 and was retailed at $150.

name: Logo Oblique
title: Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique
description: The Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a stylish and versatile sneaker that is perfect for any occasion. Made from high-quality materials, this sneaker features a sleek and modern design that is sure to turn heads. The upper is crafted from a combination of canvas and leather, with the iconic Dior Oblique pattern emblazoned across the sides. The sole is made from durable rubber, providing excellent traction and support. Available in a range of colors, including black, white, and blue, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a must-have for any fashion-forward individual. Whether you're dressing up for a night out or keeping it casual on the weekend, these sneakers are the perfect choice. Released in April 2019, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique retails for $950. This premium price tag is reflective of the high-quality materials and expert craftsmanship that goes into each pair. Something we love about the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the attention to detail that is evident in every aspect of the design. From the intricate Oblique pattern to the premium materials used, these sneakers are a true work of art. Our experts think that the standout feature of the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the combination of style and comfort. Despite their sleek and modern design, these sneakers are incredibly comfortable to wear, making them the perfect choice for any occasion.

name: Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
title: Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
description:
Please Note: These may or may not come with a Sneakersnstuff hangtag. To celebrate their 20th Anniversary, Stockholm-based retailer Sneakersnstuff teamed up with Jordan Brand to release the Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary, now available on StockX. Since their first store opening in 1999, Sneakersnstuff has evolved into a global powerhouse, becoming a leading contributor to the current state of the sneaker world. It is fitting that they receive their own Jordan collaboration to bring in two decades of growth.

This Jordan 1 Mid is comprised of a sail tumbled leather upper with suede overlays. Red accents on the ankle and Wings logo paired with a grey outsole and a special Sneakersnstuff hangtag completes the design. These sneakers released in December of 2019 for $140.

name: SNKRS Day Brown
title: Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown
description:
In honor of the annual "SNKRS Day" celebration, Nike designed the Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown model released in 2020. The Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown features brown, tan, beige, and khaki colors, and includes a blend of leather and mesh materials. The heels of the Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown get a date stamp in honor of SNKRS Day, and the outsoles feature a color combination that mixes white, tan, and brown.

The Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown released in August 2020 and retailed for $140.

name: Sneakersnstuff
title: New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff
description:
Sneakersnstuff and New Balance have been collaborating since 2005, releasing projects with robust storylines that represent their Stockholm background. The shop is taking a different approach to their upcoming 920 release, with a theme around vintage 1990s sportswear and old-school, "Mom & Pop" sporting goods shops.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff brings out quality materials to the new running silhouette. The sneaker is composed of a mix of forest green and orange pigskin suede. From there, hits of 3M appear on the toe and heel, while New Balance’s logo is embroidered in yellow on the tongue and heel. Finally, the midsole is constructed for comfort, featuring New Balance’s signature ENCAP cushioning system.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff released in January of 2021 for $200.

name: Schematic (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS)
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) is designed for grade school kids.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) for grade schoolers has a color scheme of white and black. The footwear features a white leather upper with black writing that reads "collar," "swoosh," "toe," "quarter," "cupsole," and more. The Nike swoosh is on the footwear side and the Jumpman logo is on the Jordan wings and tongue. The footwear has a white midsole fitted with a black rubber outsole. The black color on the outsole is the only thing that contrasts the white upper.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) sold at a retail price of $100 and was released on March 29th, 2022.

name: Sneaker Politics Always Ready
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Sneaker Politics Always Ready
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard design was inspired by Sneaker Politics Founder and CEO Derek Curry’s time in the Army. This pair features rich green/black canvas colorway underlays that mimic military gear, including Neoprene detailing with an American flag pattern at the toe box and an embroidered Politics letter "P" branding at the heel.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard silhouette retains its signature split-tongue formation and has a comfortable rubber outsole with GEL technology for optimal impact absorption.

ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard launched in May 2022 and was retailed at $150.

Made from high-quality materials, this sneaker features a sleek and modern design that is sure to turn heads. The upper is crafted from a combination of canvas and leather, with the iconic Dior Oblique pattern emblazoned across the sides. The sole is made from durable rubber, providing excellent traction and support. Available in a range of colors, including black, white, and blue, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a must-have for any fashion-forward individual. Whether you're dressing up for a night out or keeping it casual on the weekend, these sneakers are the perfect choice. Released in April 2019, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique retails for $950. This premium price tag is reflective of the high-quality materials and expert craftsmanship that goes into each pair. Something we love about the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the attention to detail that is evident in every aspect of the design. From the intricate Oblique pattern to the premium materials used, these sneakers are a true work of art. Our experts think that the standout feature of the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the combination of style and comfort. name: Sneakersnstuff
title: New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff
description:
Sneakersnstuff and New Balance have been collaborating since 2005, releasing projects with robust storylines that represent their Stockholm background. The shop is taking a different approach to their upcoming 920 release, with a theme around vintage 1990s sportswear and old-school, "Mom & Pop" sporting goods shops.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff brings out quality materials to the new running silhouette. The sneaker is composed of a mix of forest green and orange pigskin suede. From there, hits of 3M appear on the toe and heel, while New Balance’s logo is embroidered in yellow on the tongue and heel. Finally, the midsole is constructed for comfort, featuring New Balance’s signature ENCAP cushioning system.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff released in January of 2021 for $200.

name: Schematic (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS)
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) is designed for grade school kids.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) for grade schoolers has a color scheme of white and black. The footwear features a white leather upper with black writing that reads "collar," "swoosh," "toe," "quarter," "cupsole," and more. The Nike swoosh is on the footwear side and the Jumpman logo is on the Jordan wings and tongue. The footwear has a white midsole fitted with a black rubber outsole. The black color on the outsole is the only thing that contrasts the white upper.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) sold at a retail price of $100 and was released on March 29th, 2022.

name: Sneaker Politics Always Ready
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Sneaker Politics Always Ready
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard design was inspired by Sneaker Politics Founder and CEO Derek Curry’s time in the Army. This pair features rich green/black canvas colorway underlays that mimic military gear, including Neoprene detailing with an American flag pattern at the toe box and an embroidered Politics letter "P" branding at the heel.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard silhouette retains its signature split-tongue formation and has a comfortable rubber outsole with GEL technology for optimal impact absorption.

ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard launched in May 2022 and was retailed at $150.

name: Logo Oblique
title: Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique
description: The Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a stylish and versatile sneaker that is perfect for any occasion. Made from high-quality materials, this sneaker features a sleek and modern design that is sure to turn heads. The upper is crafted from a combination of canvas and leather, with the iconic Dior Oblique pattern emblazoned across the sides. The sole is made from durable rubber, providing excellent traction and support. Available in a range of colors, including black, white, and blue, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a must-have for any fashion-forward individual. Whether you're dressing up for a night out or keeping it casual on the weekend, these sneakers are the perfect choice. Released in April 2019, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique retails for $950. This premium price tag is reflective of the high-quality materials and expert craftsmanship that goes into each pair. Something we love about the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the attention to detail that is evident in every aspect of the design. From the intricate Oblique pattern to the premium materials used, these sneakers are a true work of art. Our experts think that the standout feature of the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the combination of style and comfort. Despite their sleek and modern design, these sneakers are incredibly comfortable to wear, making them the perfect choice for any occasion.

name: Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
title: Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
description:
Please Note: These may or may not come with a Sneakersnstuff hangtag. To celebrate their 20th Anniversary, Stockholm-based retailer Sneakersnstuff teamed up with Jordan Brand to release the Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary, now available on StockX. Since their first store opening in 1999, Sneakersnstuff has evolved into a global powerhouse, becoming a leading contributor to the current state of the sneaker world. It is fitting that they receive their own Jordan collaboration to bring in two decades of growth.

This Jordan 1 Mid is comprised of a sail tumbled leather upper with suede overlays. Red accents on the ankle and Wings logo paired with a grey outsole and a special Sneakersnstuff hangtag completes the design. These sneakers released in December of 2019 for $140.

name: Grey Iron Island Green
title: Represent x StockX Bully Sneaker (Edition of 300) Grey Iron Island Green
description: The StockX x Represent Bully collaboration celebrates the coming together of both StockX and Represent to offer an exclusive capsule for the enthusiast & collectors alike. Limited to just 300 units worldwide and developed on the latest Represent Bully model, these sneakers feature StockX colours, combining iconic style and exclusivity. Elevate your sneaker collection with this remarkable collaboration. The Bully, a retro skate-inspired sneaker. It features a ballistic nylon mesh upper, with luxury leather and suede overlays. It exhibits Represent’s initial logo in an all-over fashion on a TPU exoskeleton, with complex stitching and a final initial logo worked into the heel of the shoe. A padded collar and chunky lacing reinforce the fierce aesthetic, whilst the two-tone skate-inspired outsole unit fortifies ultimate comfort.

Something we love about the Balenciaga Track White Orange is its ability to blend fashion and function seamlessly. The shoe is not only stylish but also comfortable and practical for everyday wear. If you're looking for a statement piece that will turn heads, the Balenciaga Track White Orange is the perfect choice.

name: Sneakersnstuff
title: New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff
description:
Sneakersnstuff and New Balance have been collaborating since 2005, releasing projects with robust storylines that represent their Stockholm background. The shop is taking a different approach to their upcoming 920 release, with a theme around vintage 1990s sportswear and old-school, "Mom & Pop" sporting goods shops.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff brings out quality materials to the new running silhouette. The sneaker is composed of a mix of forest green and orange pigskin suede. From there, hits of 3M appear on the toe and heel, while New Balance’s logo is embroidered in yellow on the tongue and heel. Finally, the midsole is constructed for comfort, featuring New Balance’s signature ENCAP cushioning system.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff released in January of 2021 for $200.

name: Schematic (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS)
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) is designed for grade school kids.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) for grade schoolers has a color scheme of white and black. The footwear features a white leather upper with black writing that reads "collar," "swoosh," "toe," "quarter," "cupsole," and more. The Nike swoosh is on the footwear side and the Jumpman logo is on the Jordan wings and tongue. The footwear has a white midsole fitted with a black rubber outsole. The black color on the outsole is the only thing that contrasts the white upper.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) sold at a retail price of $100 and was released on March 29th, 2022.

name: Sneaker Politics Always Ready
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Sneaker Politics Always Ready
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard design was inspired by Sneaker Politics Founder and CEO Derek Curry’s time in the Army. This pair features rich green/black canvas colorway underlays that mimic military gear, including Neoprene detailing with an American flag pattern at the toe box and an embroidered Politics letter "P" branding at the heel.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard silhouette retains its signature split-tongue formation and has a comfortable rubber outsole with GEL technology for optimal impact absorption.

ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard launched in May 2022 and was retailed at $150.

name: Logo Oblique
title: Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique
description: The Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a stylish and versatile sneaker that is perfect for any occasion. Made from high-quality materials, this sneaker features a sleek and modern design that is sure to turn heads. The upper is crafted from a combination of canvas and leather, with the iconic Dior Oblique pattern emblazoned across the sides. The sole is made from durable rubber, providing excellent traction and support. Available in a range of colors, including black, white, and blue, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a must-have for any fashion-forward individual. Whether you're dressing up for a night out or keeping it casual on the weekend, these sneakers are the perfect choice. Released in April 2019, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique retails for $950. This premium price tag is reflective of the high-quality materials and expert craftsmanship that goes into each pair. Something we love about the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the attention to detail that is evident in every aspect of the design. From the intricate Oblique pattern to the premium materials used, these sneakers are a true work of art. Our experts think that the standout feature of the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the combination of style and comfort. Despite their sleek and modern design, these sneakers are incredibly comfortable to wear, making them the perfect choice for any occasion.

name: Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
title: Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
description:
Please Note: These may or may not come with a Sneakersnstuff hangtag. To celebrate their 20th Anniversary, Stockholm-based retailer Sneakersnstuff teamed up with Jordan Brand to release the Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary, now available on StockX. Since their first store opening in 1999, Sneakersnstuff has evolved into a global powerhouse, becoming a leading contributor to the current state of the sneaker world. It is fitting that they receive their own Jordan collaboration to bring in two decades of growth.

This Jordan 1 Mid is comprised of a sail tumbled leather upper with suede overlays. Red accents on the ankle and Wings logo paired with a grey outsole and a special Sneakersnstuff hangtag completes the design. These sneakers released in December of 2019 for $140.

name: SNKRS Day Brown
title: Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown
description:
In honor of the annual "SNKRS Day" celebration, Nike designed the Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown model released in 2020. The Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown features brown, tan, beige, and khaki colors, and includes a blend of leather and mesh materials. The heels of the Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown get a date stamp in honor of SNKRS Day, and the outsoles feature a color combination that mixes white, tan, and brown.

The Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown released in August 2020 and retailed for $140.

name: Grey Iron Island Green
title: Represent x StockX Bully Sneaker (Edition of 300) Grey Iron Island Green
description: The StockX x Represent Bully collaboration celebrates the coming together of both StockX and Represent to offer an exclusive capsule for the enthusiast & collectors alike. Limited to just 300 units worldwide and developed on the latest Represent Bully model, these sneakers feature StockX colours, combining iconic style and exclusivity. Elevate your sneaker collection with this remarkable collaboration. The Bully, a retro skate-inspired sneaker. It features a ballistic nylon mesh upper, with luxury leather and suede overlays. It exhibits Represent’s initial logo in an all-over fashion on a TPU exoskeleton, with complex stitching and a final initial logo worked into the heel of the shoe. A padded collar and chunky lacing reinforce the fierce aesthetic, whilst the two-tone skate-inspired outsole unit fortifies ultimate comfort.

title: Balenciaga Track White Orange
description: The Balenciaga Track White Orange is a highly sought-after sneaker that was released on September 3, 2018, with a retail price of $1120. This shoe features a white and orange colorway that is eye-catching and unique. The upper is made of a combination of mesh, nylon, and rubber materials, which provide both durability and breathability. The shoe also features a chunky sole that is both comfortable and stylish. One of the standout features of the Balenciaga Track White Orange is its attention to detail. The shoe features a complex layering system that creates a dynamic and textured look. The orange accents on the shoe add a pop of color that makes it stand out from other sneakers on the market. Something we love about the Balenciaga Track White Orange is its ability to blend fashion and function seamlessly. The shoe is not only stylish but also comfortable and practical for everyday wear. Our experts think that the best features of this shoe are its unique design and attention to detail. If you're looking for a statement piece that will turn heads, the Balenciaga Track White Orange is the perfect choice.

name: Sneakersnstuff
title: New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff
description:
Sneakersnstuff and New Balance have been collaborating since 2005, releasing projects with robust storylines that represent their Stockholm background. The shop is taking a different approach to their upcoming 920 release, with a theme around vintage 1990s sportswear and old-school, "Mom & Pop" sporting goods shops.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff brings out quality materials to the new running silhouette. The sneaker is composed of a mix of forest green and orange pigskin suede. From there, hits of 3M appear on the toe and heel, while New Balance’s logo is embroidered in yellow on the tongue and heel. Finally, the midsole is constructed for comfort, featuring New Balance’s signature ENCAP cushioning system.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff released in January of 2021 for $200.

The footwear features a white leather upper with black writing that reads "collar," "swoosh," "toe," "quarter," "cupsole," and more. The Nike swoosh is on the footwear side and the Jumpman logo is on the Jordan wings and tongue. The footwear has a white midsole fitted with a black rubber outsole. The black color on the outsole is the only thing that contrasts the white upper.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) sold at a retail price of $100 and was released on March 29th, 2022.

name: Sneaker Politics Always Ready

description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard design was inspired by Sneaker Politics Founder and CEO Derek Curry’s time in the Army. This pair features rich green/black canvas colorway underlays that mimic military gear, including Neoprene detailing with an American flag pattern at the toe box and an embroidered Politics letter "P" branding at the heel.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard silhouette retains its signature split-tongue formation and has a comfortable rubber outsole with GEL technology for optimal impact absorption.

ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard launched in May 2022 and was retailed at $150.

name: Logo Oblique
title: Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique
description: The Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a stylish and versatile sneaker that is perfect for any occasion. Made from high-quality materials, this sneaker features a sleek and modern design that is sure to turn heads. The upper is crafted from a combination of canvas and leather, with the iconic Dior Oblique pattern emblazoned across the sides. The sole is made from durable rubber, providing excellent traction and support. Available in a range of colors, including black, white, and blue, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a must-have for any fashion-forward individual. Whether you're dressing up for a night out or keeping it casual on the weekend, these sneakers are the perfect choice. Released in April 2019, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique retails for $950. This premium price tag is reflective of the high-quality materials and expert craftsmanship that goes into each pair. Something we love about the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the attention to detail that is evident in every aspect of the design. From the intricate Oblique pattern to the premium materials used, these sneakers are a true work of art. Our experts think that the standout feature of the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the combination of style and comfort. Despite their sleek and modern design, these sneakers are incredibly comfortable to wear, making them the perfect choice for any occasion.

name: Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
title: Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
description:
Please Note: These may or may not come with a Sneakersnstuff hangtag. To celebrate their 20th Anniversary, Stockholm-based retailer Sneakersnstuff teamed up with Jordan Brand to release the Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary, now available on StockX. Since their first store opening in 1999, Sneakersnstuff has evolved into a global powerhouse, becoming a leading contributor to the current state of the sneaker world. It is fitting that they receive their own Jordan collaboration to bring in two decades of growth.

This Jordan 1 Mid is comprised of a sail tumbled leather upper with suede overlays. Red accents on the ankle and Wings logo paired with a grey outsole and a special Sneakersnstuff hangtag completes the design. These sneakers released in December of 2019 for $140.

name: SNKRS Day Brown
title: Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown
description:
In honor of the annual "SNKRS Day" celebration, Nike designed the Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown model released in 2020. The Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown features brown, tan, beige, and khaki colors, and includes a blend of leather and mesh materials. The heels of the Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown get a date stamp in honor of SNKRS Day, and the outsoles feature a color combination that mixes white, tan, and brown.

The Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown released in August 2020 and retailed for $140.

name: Sneakersnstuff
title: New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff
description:
Sneakersnstuff and New Balance have been collaborating since 2005, releasing projects with robust storylines that represent their Stockholm background. The shop is taking a different approach to their upcoming 920 release, with a theme around vintage 1990s sportswear and old-school, "Mom & Pop" sporting goods shops.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff brings out quality materials to the new running silhouette. The sneaker is composed of a mix of forest green and orange pigskin suede. From there, hits of 3M appear on the toe and heel, while New Balance’s logo is embroidered in yellow on the tongue and heel. Finally, the midsole is constructed for comfort, featuring New Balance’s signature ENCAP cushioning system.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff released in January of 2021 for $200.

name: Schematic (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS)
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) is designed for grade school kids.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) for grade schoolers has a color scheme of white and black. The footwear features a white leather upper with black writing that reads "collar," "swoosh," "toe," "quarter," "cupsole," and more. The Nike swoosh is on the footwear side and the Jumpman logo is on the Jordan wings and tongue. The footwear has a white midsole fitted with a black rubber outsole. The black color on the outsole is the only thing that contrasts the white upper.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) sold at a retail price of $100 and was released on March 29th, 2022.

name: Sneaker Politics Always Ready
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Sneaker Politics Always Ready
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard design was inspired by Sneaker Politics Founder and CEO Derek Curry’s time in the Army. This pair features rich green/black canvas colorway underlays that mimic military gear, including Neoprene detailing with an American flag pattern at the toe box and an embroidered Politics letter "P" branding at the heel.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard silhouette retains its signature split-tongue formation and has a comfortable rubber outsole with GEL technology for optimal impact absorption.

ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard launched in May 2022 and was retailed at $150.

Made from high-quality materials, this sneaker features a sleek and modern design that is sure to turn heads. The upper is crafted from a combination of canvas and leather, with the iconic Dior Oblique pattern emblazoned across the sides. The sole is made from durable rubber, providing excellent traction and support. Available in a range of colors, including black, white, and blue, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a must-have for any fashion-forward individual. Whether you're dressing up for a night out or keeping it casual on the weekend, these sneakers are the perfect choice. Released in April 2019, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique retails for $950. This premium price tag is reflective of the high-quality materials and expert craftsmanship that goes into each pair. Something we love about the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the attention to detail that is evident in every aspect of the design. From the intricate Oblique pattern to the premium materials used, these sneakers are a true work of art. Our experts think that the standout feature of the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the combination of style and comfort. name: Sneakersnstuff
title: New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff
description:
Sneakersnstuff and New Balance have been collaborating since 2005, releasing projects with robust storylines that represent their Stockholm background. The shop is taking a different approach to their upcoming 920 release, with a theme around vintage 1990s sportswear and old-school, "Mom & Pop" sporting goods shops.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff brings out quality materials to the new running silhouette. The sneaker is composed of a mix of forest green and orange pigskin suede. From there, hits of 3M appear on the toe and heel, while New Balance’s logo is embroidered in yellow on the tongue and heel. Finally, the midsole is constructed for comfort, featuring New Balance’s signature ENCAP cushioning system.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff released in January of 2021 for $200.

name: Schematic (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS)
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) is designed for grade school kids.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) for grade schoolers has a color scheme of white and black. The footwear features a white leather upper with black writing that reads "collar," "swoosh," "toe," "quarter," "cupsole," and more. The Nike swoosh is on the footwear side and the Jumpman logo is on the Jordan wings and tongue. The footwear has a white midsole fitted with a black rubber outsole. The black color on the outsole is the only thing that contrasts the white upper.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) sold at a retail price of $100 and was released on March 29th, 2022.

name: Sneaker Politics Always Ready
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Sneaker Politics Always Ready
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard design was inspired by Sneaker Politics Founder and CEO Derek Curry’s time in the Army. This pair features rich green/black canvas colorway underlays that mimic military gear, including Neoprene detailing with an American flag pattern at the toe box and an embroidered Politics letter "P" branding at the heel.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard silhouette retains its signature split-tongue formation and has a comfortable rubber outsole with GEL technology for optimal impact absorption.

ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard launched in May 2022 and was retailed at $150.

name: Logo Oblique
title: Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique
description: The Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a stylish and versatile sneaker that is perfect for any occasion. Made from high-quality materials, this sneaker features a sleek and modern design that is sure to turn heads. The upper is crafted from a combination of canvas and leather, with the iconic Dior Oblique pattern emblazoned across the sides. The sole is made from durable rubber, providing excellent traction and support. Available in a range of colors, including black, white, and blue, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a must-have for any fashion-forward individual. Whether you're dressing up for a night out or keeping it casual on the weekend, these sneakers are the perfect choice. Released in April 2019, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique retails for $950. This premium price tag is reflective of the high-quality materials and expert craftsmanship that goes into each pair. Something we love about the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the attention to detail that is evident in every aspect of the design. From the intricate Oblique pattern to the premium materials used, these sneakers are a true work of art. Our experts think that the standout feature of the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the combination of style and comfort. Despite their sleek and modern design, these sneakers are incredibly comfortable to wear, making them the perfect choice for any occasion.

name: Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
title: Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
description:
Please Note: These may or may not come with a Sneakersnstuff hangtag. To celebrate their 20th Anniversary, Stockholm-based retailer Sneakersnstuff teamed up with Jordan Brand to release the Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary, now available on StockX. Since their first store opening in 1999, Sneakersnstuff has evolved into a global powerhouse, becoming a leading contributor to the current state of the sneaker world. It is fitting that they receive their own Jordan collaboration to bring in two decades of growth.

This Jordan 1 Mid is comprised of a sail tumbled leather upper with suede overlays. Red accents on the ankle and Wings logo paired with a grey outsole and a special Sneakersnstuff hangtag completes the design. These sneakers released in December of 2019 for $140.

name: Grey Iron Island Green
title: Represent x StockX Bully Sneaker (Edition of 300) Grey Iron Island Green
description: The StockX x Represent Bully collaboration celebrates the coming together of both StockX and Represent to offer an exclusive capsule for the enthusiast & collectors alike. Limited to just 300 units worldwide and developed on the latest Represent Bully model, these sneakers feature StockX colours, combining iconic style and exclusivity. Elevate your sneaker collection with this remarkable collaboration. The Bully, a retro skate-inspired sneaker. It features a ballistic nylon mesh upper, with luxury leather and suede overlays. It exhibits Represent’s initial logo in an all-over fashion on a TPU exoskeleton, with complex stitching and a final initial logo worked into the heel of the shoe. A padded collar and chunky lacing reinforce the fierce aesthetic, whilst the two-tone skate-inspired outsole unit fortifies ultimate comfort.

Something we love about the Balenciaga Track White Orange is its ability to blend fashion and function seamlessly. The shoe is not only stylish but also comfortable and practical for everyday wear. If you're looking for a statement piece that will turn heads, the Balenciaga Track White Orange is the perfect choice.

name: Sneakersnstuff
title: New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff
description:
Sneakersnstuff and New Balance have been collaborating since 2005, releasing projects with robust storylines that represent their Stockholm background. The shop is taking a different approach to their upcoming 920 release, with a theme around vintage 1990s sportswear and old-school, "Mom & Pop" sporting goods shops.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff brings out quality materials to the new running silhouette. The sneaker is composed of a mix of forest green and orange pigskin suede. From there, hits of 3M appear on the toe and heel, while New Balance’s logo is embroidered in yellow on the tongue and heel. Finally, the midsole is constructed for comfort, featuring New Balance’s signature ENCAP cushioning system.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff released in January of 2021 for $200.

name: Schematic (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS)
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) is designed for grade school kids.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) for grade schoolers has a color scheme of white and black. The footwear features a white leather upper with black writing that reads "collar," "swoosh," "toe," "quarter," "cupsole," and more. The Nike swoosh is on the footwear side and the Jumpman logo is on the Jordan wings and tongue. The footwear has a white midsole fitted with a black rubber outsole. The black color on the outsole is the only thing that contrasts the white upper.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) sold at a retail price of $100 and was released on March 29th, 2022.

name: Sneaker Politics Always Ready
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Sneaker Politics Always Ready
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard design was inspired by Sneaker Politics Founder and CEO Derek Curry’s time in the Army. This pair features rich green/black canvas colorway underlays that mimic military gear, including Neoprene detailing with an American flag pattern at the toe box and an embroidered Politics letter "P" branding at the heel.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard silhouette retains its signature split-tongue formation and has a comfortable rubber outsole with GEL technology for optimal impact absorption.

ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard launched in May 2022 and was retailed at $150.

name: Logo Oblique
title: Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique
description: The Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a stylish and versatile sneaker that is perfect for any occasion. Made from high-quality materials, this sneaker features a sleek and modern design that is sure to turn heads. The upper is crafted from a combination of canvas and leather, with the iconic Dior Oblique pattern emblazoned across the sides. The sole is made from durable rubber, providing excellent traction and support. Available in a range of colors, including black, white, and blue, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a must-have for any fashion-forward individual. Whether you're dressing up for a night out or keeping it casual on the weekend, these sneakers are the perfect choice. Released in April 2019, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique retails for $950. This premium price tag is reflective of the high-quality materials and expert craftsmanship that goes into each pair. Something we love about the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the attention to detail that is evident in every aspect of the design. From the intricate Oblique pattern to the premium materials used, these sneakers are a true work of art. Our experts think that the standout feature of the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the combination of style and comfort. Despite their sleek and modern design, these sneakers are incredibly comfortable to wear, making them the perfect choice for any occasion.

name: Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
title: Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
description:
Please Note: These may or may not come with a Sneakersnstuff hangtag. To celebrate their 20th Anniversary, Stockholm-based retailer Sneakersnstuff teamed up with Jordan Brand to release the Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary, now available on StockX. Since their first store opening in 1999, Sneakersnstuff has evolved into a global powerhouse, becoming a leading contributor to the current state of the sneaker world. It is fitting that they receive their own Jordan collaboration to bring in two decades of growth.

This Jordan 1 Mid is comprised of a sail tumbled leather upper with suede overlays. Red accents on the ankle and Wings logo paired with a grey outsole and a special Sneakersnstuff hangtag completes the design. These sneakers released in December of 2019 for $140.

name: SNKRS Day Brown
title: Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown
description:
In honor of the annual "SNKRS Day" celebration, Nike designed the Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown model released in 2020. The Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown features brown, tan, beige, and khaki colors, and includes a blend of leather and mesh materials. The heels of the Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown get a date stamp in honor of SNKRS Day, and the outsoles feature a color combination that mixes white, tan, and brown.

The Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown released in August 2020 and retailed for $140.

name: Grey Iron Island Green
title: Represent x StockX Bully Sneaker (Edition of 300) Grey Iron Island Green
description: The StockX x Represent Bully collaboration celebrates the coming together of both StockX and Represent to offer an exclusive capsule for the enthusiast & collectors alike. Limited to just 300 units worldwide and developed on the latest Represent Bully model, these sneakers feature StockX colours, combining iconic style and exclusivity. Elevate your sneaker collection with this remarkable collaboration. The Bully, a retro skate-inspired sneaker. It features a ballistic nylon mesh upper, with luxury leather and suede overlays. It exhibits Represent’s initial logo in an all-over fashion on a TPU exoskeleton, with complex stitching and a final initial logo worked into the heel of the shoe. A padded collar and chunky lacing reinforce the fierce aesthetic, whilst the two-tone skate-inspired outsole unit fortifies ultimate comfort.

title: Balenciaga Track White Orange
description: The Balenciaga Track White Orange is a highly sought-after sneaker that was released on September 3, 2018, with a retail price of $1120. This shoe features a white and orange colorway that is eye-catching and unique. The upper is made of a combination of mesh, nylon, and rubber materials, which provide both durability and breathability. The shoe also features a chunky sole that is both comfortable and stylish. One of the standout features of the Balenciaga Track White Orange is its attention to detail. The shoe features a complex layering system that creates a dynamic and textured look. The orange accents on the shoe add a pop of color that makes it stand out from other sneakers on the market. Something we love about the Balenciaga Track White Orange is its ability to blend fashion and function seamlessly. The shoe is not only stylish but also comfortable and practical for everyday wear. Our experts think that the best features of this shoe are its unique design and attention to detail. If you're looking for a statement piece that will turn heads, the Balenciaga Track White Orange is the perfect choice.

name: Sneakersnstuff
title: New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff
description:
Sneakersnstuff and New Balance have been collaborating since 2005, releasing projects with robust storylines that represent their Stockholm background. The shop is taking a different approach to their upcoming 920 release, with a theme around vintage 1990s sportswear and old-school, "Mom & Pop" sporting goods shops.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff brings out quality materials to the new running silhouette. The sneaker is composed of a mix of forest green and orange pigskin suede. From there, hits of 3M appear on the toe and heel, while New Balance’s logo is embroidered in yellow on the tongue and heel. Finally, the midsole is constructed for comfort, featuring New Balance’s signature ENCAP cushioning system.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff released in January of 2021 for $200.

The footwear features a white leather upper with black writing that reads "collar," "swoosh," "toe," "quarter," "cupsole," and more. The Nike swoosh is on the footwear side and the Jumpman logo is on the Jordan wings and tongue. The footwear has a white midsole fitted with a black rubber outsole. The black color on the outsole is the only thing that contrasts the white upper.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) sold at a retail price of $100 and was released on March 29th, 2022.

name: Sneaker Politics Always Ready

description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard design was inspired by Sneaker Politics Founder and CEO Derek Curry’s time in the Army. This pair features rich green/black canvas colorway underlays that mimic military gear, including Neoprene detailing with an American flag pattern at the toe box and an embroidered Politics letter "P" branding at the heel.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard silhouette retains its signature split-tongue formation and has a comfortable rubber outsole with GEL technology for optimal impact absorption.

ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard launched in May 2022 and was retailed at $150.

name: Logo Oblique
title: Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique
description: The Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a stylish and versatile sneaker that is perfect for any occasion. Made from high-quality materials, this sneaker features a sleek and modern design that is sure to turn heads. The upper is crafted from a combination of canvas and leather, with the iconic Dior Oblique pattern emblazoned across the sides. The sole is made from durable rubber, providing excellent traction and support. Available in a range of colors, including black, white, and blue, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a must-have for any fashion-forward individual. Whether you're dressing up for a night out or keeping it casual on the weekend, these sneakers are the perfect choice. Released in April 2019, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique retails for $950. This premium price tag is reflective of the high-quality materials and expert craftsmanship that goes into each pair. Something we love about the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the attention to detail that is evident in every aspect of the design. From the intricate Oblique pattern to the premium materials used, these sneakers are a true work of art. Our experts think that the standout feature of the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the combination of style and comfort. Despite their sleek and modern design, these sneakers are incredibly comfortable to wear, making them the perfect choice for any occasion.

name: Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
title: Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
description:
Please Note: These may or may not come with a Sneakersnstuff hangtag. To celebrate their 20th Anniversary, Stockholm-based retailer Sneakersnstuff teamed up with Jordan Brand to release the Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary, now available on StockX. Since their first store opening in 1999, Sneakersnstuff has evolved into a global powerhouse, becoming a leading contributor to the current state of the sneaker world. It is fitting that they receive their own Jordan collaboration to bring in two decades of growth.

This Jordan 1 Mid is comprised of a sail tumbled leather upper with suede overlays. Red accents on the ankle and Wings logo paired with a grey outsole and a special Sneakersnstuff hangtag completes the design. These sneakers released in December of 2019 for $140.

name: SNKRS Day Brown
title: Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown
description:
In honor of the annual "SNKRS Day" celebration, Nike designed the Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown model released in 2020. The Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown features brown, tan, beige, and khaki colors, and includes a blend of leather and mesh materials. The heels of the Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown get a date stamp in honor of SNKRS Day, and the outsoles feature a color combination that mixes white, tan, and brown.

The Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown released in August 2020 and retailed for $140.

name: Sneakersnstuff
title: New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff
description:
Sneakersnstuff and New Balance have been collaborating since 2005, releasing projects with robust storylines that represent their Stockholm background. The shop is taking a different approach to their upcoming 920 release, with a theme around vintage 1990s sportswear and old-school, "Mom & Pop" sporting goods shops.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff brings out quality materials to the new running silhouette. The sneaker is composed of a mix of forest green and orange pigskin suede. From there, hits of 3M appear on the toe and heel, while New Balance’s logo is embroidered in yellow on the tongue and heel. Finally, the midsole is constructed for comfort, featuring New Balance’s signature ENCAP cushioning system.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff released in January of 2021 for $200.

name: Schematic (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS)
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) is designed for grade school kids.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) for grade schoolers has a color scheme of white and black. The footwear features a white leather upper with black writing that reads "collar," "swoosh," "toe," "quarter," "cupsole," and more. The Nike swoosh is on the footwear side and the Jumpman logo is on the Jordan wings and tongue. The footwear has a white midsole fitted with a black rubber outsole. The black color on the outsole is the only thing that contrasts the white upper.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) sold at a retail price of $100 and was released on March 29th, 2022.

name: Sneaker Politics Always Ready
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Sneaker Politics Always Ready
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard design was inspired by Sneaker Politics Founder and CEO Derek Curry’s time in the Army. This pair features rich green/black canvas colorway underlays that mimic military gear, including Neoprene detailing with an American flag pattern at the toe box and an embroidered Politics letter "P" branding at the heel.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard silhouette retains its signature split-tongue formation and has a comfortable rubber outsole with GEL technology for optimal impact absorption.

ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard launched in May 2022 and was retailed at $150.

Made from high-quality materials, this sneaker features a sleek and modern design that is sure to turn heads. The upper is crafted from a combination of canvas and leather, with the iconic Dior Oblique pattern emblazoned across the sides. The sole is made from durable rubber, providing excellent traction and support. Available in a range of colors, including black, white, and blue, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a must-have for any fashion-forward individual. Whether you're dressing up for a night out or keeping it casual on the weekend, these sneakers are the perfect choice. Released in April 2019, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique retails for $950. This premium price tag is reflective of the high-quality materials and expert craftsmanship that goes into each pair. Something we love about the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the attention to detail that is evident in every aspect of the design. From the intricate Oblique pattern to the premium materials used, these sneakers are a true work of art. Our experts think that the standout feature of the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the combination of style and comfort. name: Sneakersnstuff
title: New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff
description:
Sneakersnstuff and New Balance have been collaborating since 2005, releasing projects with robust storylines that represent their Stockholm background. The shop is taking a different approach to their upcoming 920 release, with a theme around vintage 1990s sportswear and old-school, "Mom & Pop" sporting goods shops.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff brings out quality materials to the new running silhouette. The sneaker is composed of a mix of forest green and orange pigskin suede. From there, hits of 3M appear on the toe and heel, while New Balance’s logo is embroidered in yellow on the tongue and heel. Finally, the midsole is constructed for comfort, featuring New Balance’s signature ENCAP cushioning system.

The New Balance 920 Sneakersnstuff released in January of 2021 for $200.

name: Schematic (GS)
title: Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS)
description:
The Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) is designed for grade school kids.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) for grade schoolers has a color scheme of white and black. The footwear features a white leather upper with black writing that reads "collar," "swoosh," "toe," "quarter," "cupsole," and more. The Nike swoosh is on the footwear side and the Jumpman logo is on the Jordan wings and tongue. The footwear has a white midsole fitted with a black rubber outsole. The black color on the outsole is the only thing that contrasts the white upper.
​
Jordan 1 Mid Schematic (GS) sold at a retail price of $100 and was released on March 29th, 2022.

name: Sneaker Politics Always Ready
title: ASICS Gel-Lyte III Sneaker Politics Always Ready
description:
The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard design was inspired by Sneaker Politics Founder and CEO Derek Curry’s time in the Army. This pair features rich green/black canvas colorway underlays that mimic military gear, including Neoprene detailing with an American flag pattern at the toe box and an embroidered Politics letter "P" branding at the heel.

The ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard silhouette retains its signature split-tongue formation and has a comfortable rubber outsole with GEL technology for optimal impact absorption.

ASICS Gel Lyte III Sneaker Politics Courtyard launched in May 2022 and was retailed at $150.

name: Logo Oblique
title: Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique
description: The Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a stylish and versatile sneaker that is perfect for any occasion. Made from high-quality materials, this sneaker features a sleek and modern design that is sure to turn heads. The upper is crafted from a combination of canvas and leather, with the iconic Dior Oblique pattern emblazoned across the sides. The sole is made from durable rubber, providing excellent traction and support. Available in a range of colors, including black, white, and blue, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is a must-have for any fashion-forward individual. Whether you're dressing up for a night out or keeping it casual on the weekend, these sneakers are the perfect choice. Released in April 2019, the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique retails for $950. This premium price tag is reflective of the high-quality materials and expert craftsmanship that goes into each pair. Something we love about the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the attention to detail that is evident in every aspect of the design. From the intricate Oblique pattern to the premium materials used, these sneakers are a true work of art. Our experts think that the standout feature of the Dior B23 Low Top Logo Oblique is the combination of style and comfort. Despite their sleek and modern design, these sneakers are incredibly comfortable to wear, making them the perfect choice for any occasion.

name: Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
title: Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary
description:
Please Note: These may or may not come with a Sneakersnstuff hangtag. To celebrate their 20th Anniversary, Stockholm-based retailer Sneakersnstuff teamed up with Jordan Brand to release the Jordan 1 Mid Sneakersnstuff 20th Anniversary, now available on StockX. Since their first store opening in 1999, Sneakersnstuff has evolved into a global powerhouse, becoming a leading contributor to the current state of the sneaker world. It is fitting that they receive their own Jordan collaboration to bring in two decades of growth.

This Jordan 1 Mid is comprised of a sail tumbled leather upper with suede overlays. Red accents on the ankle and Wings logo paired with a grey outsole and a special Sneakersnstuff hangtag completes the design. These sneakers released in December of 2019 for $140.

name: SNKRS Day Brown
title: Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown
description:
In honor of the annual "SNKRS Day" celebration, Nike designed the Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown model released in 2020. The Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown features brown, tan, beige, and khaki colors, and includes a blend of leather and mesh materials. The heels of the Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown get a date stamp in honor of SNKRS Day, and the outsoles feature a color combination that mixes white, tan, and brown.

The Nike Air Max 1 SNKRS Day Brown released in August 2020 and retailed for $140.
